ve Jamison and Craig Walsh, ''The Score Takes Care of Itself: My Philosophy of Leadership''. Penguin Group Publishing, 2009 ({{ISBN|978-1-59184-266-8}}).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Profootballhof|id=224|name=Bill Walsh}}\n\n{{Stanford Cardinal football coach navbox}}\n{{San Francisco 49ers coach navbox}}\n{{San Francisco 49ers general manager navbox}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Merlin Olsen]]}} \n{{s-ttl|title=''[[NFL on NBC]]'' lead analyst|years=1989\u20131991}} \n{{s-aft|after=[[Bob Trumpy]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Pac-12 Coach of the Year}}\n{{AP NFL Coaches of the Year}}\n{{Super Bowl XVI}}\n{{Super Bowl XIX}}\n{{Super Bowl XXIII}}\n{{NFL1980s}}\n{{NFL100}}\n{{1993 Football HOF}}\n{{Pro Football Hall of Fame members}}\n{{Amos Alonzo Stagg Award}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Portal bar|American football|Biography|College football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Walsh, Bill}}\n[[Category:1931 births]]\n[[Category:2007 deaths]]\n[[Category:American memoirists]]\n[[Category:American motivational writers]]\n[[Category:Cincinnati Bengals coaches]]\n[[Category:California Golden Bears football coaches]]\n[[Category:College football announcers]]\n[[Category:Continental Football League coaches]]\n[[Category:National Football League announcers]]\n[[Category:National Football League general managers]]\n[[Category:Notre Dame Fighting Irish football broadcasters]]\n[[Category:Oakland Raiders coaches]]\n[[Category:San Diego Chargers coaches]]\n[[Category:San Francisco 49ers head coaches]]\n[[Category:San Francisco 49ers executives]]\n[[Category:San Jose State University alumni]]\n[[Category:San Jose State Spartans football coaches]]\n[[Category:San Jose State Spartans football players]]\n[[Category:Stanford Cardinal football coaches]]\n[[Category:High school football coaches in California]]\n[[Category:Pro Football Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl-winning head coaches]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Hayward, California]]\n[[Category:Sportspeop