{"title_page": "SC Verl", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = SC Verl\n| image    = SC Verl logo.svg\n| image_size = 200\n| fullname = Sportclub Verl von 1924 e.V.\n| nickname = \n| founded  = 6 September 1924\n| ground   = Stadion an der Poststra\u00dfe\n| capacity = 5,001\n| chairman = Raimund Bertels\n| manager  = Guerino Capretti\n| league   = [[Regionalliga West]] (IV)\n| season   = [[2018\u201319 Regionalliga#Regionalliga West|2018\u201319]]\n| position = 7th\n| pattern_la1= | pattern_b1=_thinblacksides | pattern_ra1= | leftarm1=FFFFFF | body1=FFFFFF | rightarm1=FFFFFF | shorts1=FFFFFF | socks1=FFFFFF |\n  pattern_la2= | pattern_b2=_thinwhitesides | pattern_ra2= | leftarm2=000000 | body2=000000 | rightarm2=000000 | shorts2=000000 | socks2=000000 |\n}}\n\n'''SC Verl''' is a [[Football in Germany|German association football club]] based in [[Verl]], North Rhine-Westphalia. The club was founded on 6 September 1924,<ref>Gr\u00fcne, Hardy (2001). Vereinslexikon. Kassel: AGON Sportverlag {{ISBN|3-89784-147-9}}</ref> and since 1970 has consistently played in the higher echelons of amateur football.\n\n__TOC__\n\n==History==\nAfter almost 50 years of comparably insignificant existence, SC Verl advanced to the Landesliga Westfalen (IV) in 1970. Since then, SC Verl have been relegated only once (in 2003), qualified for newly introduced higher-class leagues three times out of four, won their league twice, and played the promotion round for [[2. Bundesliga]] once (in 1991). Had they advanced, SC Verl would have been the smallest town ever to field a German pro football team,. Their second bid for advancing to professional football was the 1994\u201395 season, when they finished second in the newly formed Regionalliga Nord (III), six points behind [[Arminia Bielefeld]].\n\n===German Cup appearances===\nSC Verl have appeared in the [[DFB-Pokal]] (German Cup) tournament six times. In 1979, they defeated [[VfB Oldenburg]] (III)<ref>[http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde1/oldenburg-verl/ VfB Oldenburg&nbsp;\u2013 SC Verl, 26.08.1979] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827185637/http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde1/oldenburg-verl/ |date=27 August 2011 }}</ref> and [[SV Elversberg|Spvgg Elversberg]] (IV)<ref>[http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde2/verl-elversberg/ SV Elversberg&nbsp;\u2013 SC Verl, 29.09.1979] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827190111/http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde2/verl-elversberg/ |date=27 August 2011 }}</ref> before going out to [[Stuttgarter Kickers]] (II).<ref>[http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde3/verl-stkickers/ SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 Stuttgarter Kickers, 12.01.1980] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827190235/http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde3/verl-stkickers/ |date=27 August 2011 }}</ref> In 1992, they lost an all-amateur match in the first round. In 1999, they eliminated the [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] 6\u20135 on penalties, with [[Arne Friedrich]] scoring the decisive penalty.<ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=160463 SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach, 31.07.1999]</ref> They were defeated by the Bundesliga side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in the second round.<ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=160461 SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 Eintracht Frankfurt, 08.08.1999]</ref> In both their fourth (2007) and fifth (2010) appearances, they lost their first round matches against [[TSV 1860 Munich]] (II)&nbsp;\u2013 in the 2010 match by 2\u20131 after they led 1\u20130 at half-time.<ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=503057&action=showSchema&lang=D&liga=dfbpokm&saison=07&saisonl=2007&spieltag=1&spielid=653&cHash=c793841eb3 SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 TSV 1860 M\u00fcnchen, 04.08.2007]</ref><ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=509984&no_cache=1&action=showSchema&lang=D&liga=dfbpokm&saison=10&saisonl=2010&spieltag=1&spielid=122593&cHash=e06aafd73e SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 1860 M\u00fcnchen, 14.08.2010]</ref>\n\nIn the [[2019\u201320 DFB-Pokal|2019\u201320 season]] Verl caused a major upset by beating the Bundesliga club [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]] 2\u20131 in the first round<ref>{{cite web |title=Viertligist Verl wirft Augsburg aus dem DFB-Pokal, Lautern besiegt Mainz |url=https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/dfb-pokal-viertligist-verl-wirft-bundesligist-augsburg-raus-a-1281383.html |website=Spiegel Online |accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> and 2. Bundesliga [[Holstein Kiel]] on penalties in the second round. <ref>{{cite web |title=DFB-POKAL |url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2301983 |accessdate=3 November 2019}}</ref>, before losing 1\u20130 to [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=DFB-POKAL |url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2302011 |accessdate=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Relegation and Non-Qualification===\nIn 2003, a 15th-place finish in the Regionalliga Nord (III) saw the team relegated for the first time in over thirty years. Some dispute surrounds Verl having to play the last game of the season in Paderborn during torrential rain, while [[Hamburger SV II]] were able to claim unplayable conditions and played the next day, securing a victory against [[KFC Uerdingen]] to remain in the league.<ref>[http://www.fussballdaten.de/regionalliga/nord/2003/ Regionalliga Nord 2002/03, 34th gameday]</ref>\n\nSC Verl had to play the [[Oberliga (football)|Oberliga Westfalen]] (IV) for four years before winning the championship and advancing to Regionalliga again in 2007. One season later, the [[3. Liga]] was introduced between the [[2. Bundesliga]] and the Regionalliga, which in turn was split up from two into three divisions. SC Verl suffered through a poor 2007\u201308 campaign, finishing 18th and failing to qualify for the 3. Liga. They have remained in the fourth-tier Regionalliga since.\n\n===[[2009 European football betting scandal]]===\nTwo SC Verl games from the 2008\u201309 season&nbsp;\u2013 among over two hundred games by other clubs&nbsp;\u2013 were suspected of having been rigged by players, leading to significant attention by the press as, for several days, SC Verl was the only club actually named. The two players accused were summarily suspended, and their contracts were eventually terminated.<ref>[http://www.rootdirectory.de/scv/20091217.html Neumanns Platz im Verler Kader ist frei]{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} in: ''Neue Westf\u00e4lische'', 17 December 2009</ref><ref>[http://www.scv-fans.de/03c1989d290cc7b01.php SC Verl k\u00fcndigt Hagedorn'']{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} in: ''Westfalenblatt'', 24 February 2010</ref>\n\n===Amateur success===\nHaving played at least fourth tier level since 1970, with 17 consecutive seasons in the third tier, makes SC Verl one of the most consistent top teams of Germany's amateur football. One of the smallest cities to field a fourth-tier football team, and together with neighbouring club [[SC Wiedenbr\u00fcck 2000]] one of only two clubs in the [[Regionalliga West]] working under amateur conditions (both players and coaches have day-time jobs), the club is without any liabilities&nbsp;\u2013 a direct result of a continued policy of \"no credit financing\".\n\nSince 2008 the club has been a member of the Regionalliga West, achieving mid-table finishes each season.\n\n<timeline>\n\nImageSize = width:850 height:165\nPlotArea  = width:700 height:40 left:130 bottom:65\nAlignBars = justify\n\nPeriod     = from:1970 till:2018\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nScaleMajor = unit:year increment:4 start:1970\nScaleMinor = unit:year increment:1 start:1970\n\nColors =\n  id:gruen value:rgb(0.7,1,0.7)\n  id:blau  value:rgb(0.7,0.7,1)\n  id:rot   value:rgb(1,0.7,0.7)\n  id:blau  value:rgb(0.5,0.5,1)\n  id:gelb  value:rgb(1,1,0.7)\n  id:grau  value:gray(0.8)\n\nBarData =\n  bar:3rdtier text:\"3rd Tier\"\n  bar:4thtier text:\"4th Tier\"\n\nPlotData=\n  align:center textcolor:black fontsize:8 mark:(line,grau) width:20 shift:(1,-5)\n\n  bar:3rdtier color:gruen\n  from:1986 till:1987 text:9\n  from:1987 till:1988 text:13\n  from:1988 till:1989 text:7\n  from:1989 till:1990 text:6\n  from:1990 till:1991 text:1\n  from:1991 till:1992 text:3\n  from:1992 till:1993 text:2\n  from:1993 till:1994 text:5\n  from:1994 till:1995 text:2\n  from:1995 till:1996 text:10\n  from:1996 till:1997 text:7\n  from:1997 till:1998 text:10\n  from:1998 till:1999 text:10\n  from:1999 till:2000 text:9\n  from:2000 till:2001 text:6\n  from:2001 till:2002 text:11\n  from:2002 till:2003 text:15\n  from:2007 till:2008 text:18\n\n  bar:4thtier color:gelb\n  from:1970 till:1971 text:3\n  from:1971 till:1972 text:6\n  from:1972 till:1973 text:3\n  from:1973 till:1974 text:3\n  from:1974 till:1975 text:7\n  from:1975 till:1976 text:7\n  from:1976 till:1977 text:7\n  from:1977 till:1978 text:2\n  from:1978 till:1979 text:4\n  from:1979 till:1980 text:5\n  from:1980 till:1981 text:2\n  from:1981 till:1982 text:8\n  from:1982 till:1983 text:4\n  from:1983 till:1984 text:4\n  from:1984 till:1985 text:2\n  from:1985 till:1986 text:1\n  from:2003 till:2004 text:2\n  from:2004 till:2005 text:5\n  from:2005 till:2006 text:2\n  from:2006 till:2007 text:2\n  from:2008 till:2009 text:8\n  from:2009 till:2010 text:9\n  from:2010 till:2011 text:9\n  from:2011 till:2012 text:10\n  from:2012 till:2013 text:10\n  from:2013 till:2014 text:11\n  from:2014 till:2015 text:7\n  from:2015 till:2016 text:10\n  from:2016 till:2017 text:13\n  from:2017 till:2018 text:8\n\nLineData=\n  layer:front\n  at:1978 width:0.5 color:black\n  at:1994 width:0.5 color:black\n  at:2008 width:0.5 color:black\n\nTextData= \n  pos:(15,18) fontsize:8 text:\"The third and fourth tier at their time were, respectively:\"\n  pos:(15,3) fontsize:8 text:\"Until 1978 Verbands-/Landesliga, until 1994 Ober-/Verbandsliga, until 2008 Regional-/Oberliga, and 3. Liga/Regionalliga since 2008.\"\n\n</timeline>\n\n==Honours==\nThe club's honours:\n* '''[[Oberliga Westfalen]]'''\n** Champions: 1991, 2007\n* '''[[Westphalia Cup]]'''\n** Winners: 1992, 1999, 2007\n\n==Players==\n\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|23 August 2019|<ref>{{cite web |title=Die Erste |language=German |url=http://www.sportclub-verl.de/Mannschaft/2497/Die-Erste |publisher=SC Verl |accessdate=23 August 2019}</ref>}}\n\n{{fs start}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 1|pos=GK|name=[[Sebastian Lange]]}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 3|pos=MF|name=Jan Sch\u00f6ppner}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 4|pos=DF|name=Daniel Mikic}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 5|pos=DF|name=Alessandro Otte}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 6|pos=MF|name=Ron Schallenberg}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 7|pos=MF|name=Mehmet Kurt}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 8|pos=MF|name=Hendrik Lohmar}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no= 9|pos=FW|name=Exauce Andzouana}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=10|pos=MF|name=Matthias Haeder}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=11|pos=MF|name=Jannik Schr\u00f6der}}\n{{Fs player|nat=BIH|no=13|pos=FW|name=[[Zlatko Janji\u0107]]}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=14|pos=DF|name=[[Patrick Choroba]]}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=16|pos=DF|name=[[Sergej Schmik]]}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=18|pos=FW|name=[[Ayg\u00fcn Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m]]}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=19|pos=DF|name=Yannick Langesberg}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=20|pos=MF|name=Philip Semlits}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=21|pos=DF|name=Lars Ritzka}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=22|pos=GK|name=Luis Klante}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=23|pos=DF|name=Julian St\u00f6ckner}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=24|pos=FW|name=Anton Heinz}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=26|pos=FW|name=Christopher Schepp}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=27|pos=FW|name=Fabian Brosowski}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=28|pos=DF|name=Cinar Sansar}}\n{{Fs player|nat=KOS|no=29|pos=MF|name=[[Dardan Karimani]]}}\n{{Fs player|nat=GER|no=32|pos=GK|name=Robin Br\u00fcseke}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n==Famous players==\nSC Verl has seen many players who would go on to pro careers, the most notable being [[Arne Friedrich]] who played his last amateur season with the club before joining [[Arminia Bielefeld]] in 2000. He would go on to appear for the [[Germany national football team|national side]] and captained ''[[Hertha Berlin|Hertha BSC Berlin]]''.\n\n===International players===\n* [[Musemestre Bamba]], 3 A-Games for the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo national football team]]\n* [[Ousseni Labo]], 6 A-Games for the [[Togo national football team]]\n* [[Etienne Barbara]], 30 A-Games for the [[Malta national football team]]\n* [[Heinrich Schmidtgal]], 15 A-Games for the [[Kazakhstan national football team]]\n\n==Stadium==\nAfter its establishment in 1924 and through part of the 1930s, SC Verl played at Auf der Heide. Sometime in the 1930s they moved to Birkenallee, where they remained until the end of World War II in 1945. Between 1945 and '55 their home ground was the Sportplatz Poststra\u00dfe, and after 1955 the Stadion an der Poststra\u00dfe. After capturing the Amateuroberliga Westfalen title in 1991, the team played its promotion round matches in the Heidewaldestadion G\u00fctersloh in its failed attempt to advance to the [[2. Bundesliga]] (as the Poststra\u00dfe was not up to the task both capacity- and security-wise). The Stadion an der Poststra\u00dfe was last expanded in 2015-16 to a capacity of 5,153, and renamed \"Sportclub-Arena\".\n\n==Rivalries==\nSC Verl followers share a heartfelt rivalry with nearby [[FC G\u00fctersloh]] whose supporters look down on the \"village club\", while SCV supporters in their turn tease the \"big city club\" over its inconsistent performance and financial woes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n<!--\n1970-71\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t3rd\n1971-72\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t6th\n1972-73\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t3rd\n1973-74\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t3rd\n1974-75\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t7th\n1975-76\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t7th\n1976-77\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t7th\n1977\u201378\t(V)\tLandesliga Westfalen-1\t\t2nd \u2191\n1978\u201379\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t4th\n1979\u201380\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t5th\n1980\u201381\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t2nd\n1981\u201382\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t8th\n1982\u201383\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t4th\n1983\u201384\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t4th\n1984\u201385\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t2nd\n1985\u201386\t(IV)\tVerbandsliga Westfalen-NO\t1st \u2191\n1986\u201387\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t9th\n1987\u201388\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t13th\n1988\u201389\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t7th\n1989\u201390\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t6th\n1990\u201391\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t1st\n1991\u201392\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t3rd\n1992\u201393\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t2nd\n1993\u201394\t(III)\tAm.Oberliga Westfalen\t\t5th\n1994\u201395\t(III)\tRegionalliga West/SW\t\t2nd\n1995\u201396\t(III)\tRegionalliga West/SW\t\t10th\n1996\u201397\t(III)\tRegionalliga West/SW\t\t7th\n1997\u201398\t(III)\tRegionalliga West/SW\t\t10th\n1998\u201399\t(III)\tRegionalliga West/SW\t\t10th\n1999-00\t(III)\tRegionalliga West/SW\t\t9th\n2000\u201301\t(III)\tRegionalliga Nord\t\t6th\n2001\u201302\t(III)\tRegionalliga Nord\t\t11th\n2002\u201303\t(III)\tRegionalliga Nord\t\t15th \u2193\n2003\u201304\t(IV)\tOberliga Westfalen\t\t2nd\n2004\u201305\t(IV)\tOberliga Westfalen\t\t5th\n2005\u201306\t(IV)\tOberliga Westfalen\t\t2nd\n2006\u201307\t(IV)\tOberliga Westfalen\t\t1st \u2191\n2007\u201308\t(III)\tRegionalliga Nord\t\t18th\t\t\n2008\u201309 (IV) Regionalliga West\t\t8th\n2009\u201310 (IV) Regionalliga West 9th\n2010\u201311 (IV) Regionalliga West 9th\n2011\u201312 (IV) Regionalliga West 10th\n-->\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|SC Verl}}\n* [http://www.scverl.de/ Official website] {{in lang|de}}\n* [http://www.f-archiv.de/ Das deutsche Fu\u00dfball-Archiv] historical German domestic league tables {{in lang|de}}\n* [http://www.abseits-soccer.com/clubs/verl.html Abseits Guide to German Soccer]\n\n{{Regionalliga West}}\n\n{{coord|51|53|00|N|8|30|48|E|region:DE-NW_type:landmark_source:dewiki|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Verl, Sc}}\n[[Category:Football clubs in Germany]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in North Rhine-Westphalia]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1924]]\n[[Category:SC Verl| ]]\n[[Category:1924 establishments in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = SC Verl\n| image    = SC Verl logo.svg\n| image_size = 200\n| fullname = Sportclub Verl von 1924 e.V.\n| nickname = \n| founded  = 6 September 1924\n| ground   = Stadion an der Poststra\u00dfe\n| capacity = 5,001\n| chairman = Raimund Bertels\n| manager  = Guerino Capretti\n| league   = [[Regionalliga West]] (IV)\n| season   = [[2018\u201319 Regionalliga#Regionalliga West|2018\u201319]]\n| position = 7th\n| pattern_la1= | pattern_b1=_thinblacksides | pattern_ra1= | leftarm1=FFFFFF | body1=FFFFFF | rightarm1=FFFFFF | shorts1=FFFFFF | socks1=FFFFFF |\n  pattern_la2= | pattern_b2=_thinwhitesides | pattern_ra2= | leftarm2=000000 | body2=000000 | rightarm2=000000 | shorts2=000000 | socks2=000000 |\n}}\n\n'''SC Verl''' is a [[Football in Germany|German association football club]] based in [[Verl]], North Rhine-Westphalia. The club was founded on 6 September 1924,<ref>Gr\u00fcne, Hardy (2001). Vereinslexikon. Kassel: AGON Sportverlag {{ISBN|3-89784-147-9}}</ref> and since 1970 has consistently played in the higher echelons of amateur football.\n\n__TOC__\n\n==History==\nAfter almost 50 years of comparably insignificant existence, SC Verl advanced to the Landesliga Westfalen (IV) in 1970. Since then, SC Verl have been relegated only once (in 2003), qualified for newly introduced higher-class leagues three times out of four, won their league twice, and played the promotion round for [[2. Bundesliga]] once (in 1991). Had they advanced, SC Verl would have been the smallest town ever to field a German pro football team,. Their second bid for advancing to professional football was the 1994\u201395 season, when they finished second in the newly formed Regionalliga Nord (III), six points behind [[Arminia Bielefeld]].\n\n===German Cup appearances===\nSC Verl have appeared in the [[DFB-Pokal]] (German Cup) tournament six times. In 1979, they defeated [[VfB Oldenburg]] (III)<ref>[http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde1/oldenburg-verl/ VfB Oldenburg&nbsp;\u2013 SC Verl, 26.08.1979] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827185637/http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde1/oldenburg-verl/ |date=27 August 2011 }}</ref> and [[SV Elversberg|Spvgg Elversberg]] (IV)<ref>[http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde2/verl-elversberg/ SV Elversberg&nbsp;\u2013 SC Verl, 29.09.1979] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827190111/http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde2/verl-elversberg/ |date=27 August 2011 }}</ref> before going out to [[Stuttgarter Kickers]] (II).<ref>[http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde3/verl-stkickers/ SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 Stuttgarter Kickers, 12.01.1980] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827190235/http://sport-dienst.fussball.de/dfb-pokal/1980/runde3/verl-stkickers/ |date=27 August 2011 }}</ref> In 1992, they lost an all-amateur match in the first round. In 1999, they eliminated the [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] 6\u20135 on penalties, with [[Arne Friedrich]] scoring the decisive penalty.<ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=160463 SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach, 31.07.1999]</ref> They were defeated by the Bundesliga side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in the second round.<ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=160461 SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 Eintracht Frankfurt, 08.08.1999]</ref> In both their fourth (2007) and fifth (2010) appearances, they lost their first round matches against [[TSV 1860 Munich]] (II)&nbsp;\u2013 in the 2010 match by 2\u20131 after they led 1\u20130 at half-time.<ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=503057&action=showSchema&lang=D&liga=dfbpokm&saison=07&saisonl=2007&spieltag=1&spielid=653&cHash=c793841eb3 SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 TSV 1860 M\u00fcnchen, 04.08.2007]</ref><ref>dfb.de: [https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=509984&no_cache=1&action=showSchema&lang=D&liga=dfbpokm&saison=10&saisonl=2010&spieltag=1&spielid=122593&cHash=e06aafd73e SC Verl&nbsp;\u2013 1860 M\u00fcnchen, 14.08.2010]</ref>\n\nIn the [[2019\u201320 DFB-Pokal|2019\u201320 season]] Verl caused a major upset by beating the Bundesliga club [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]] 2\u20131 in the first round<ref>{{cite web |title=Viertligist Verl wirft Augsburg aus dem DFB-Pokal, Lautern besiegt Mainz |url=https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/dfb-pokal-viertligist-verl-wirft-bundesligist-augsburg-raus-a-1281383.html |website=Spiegel Online |accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> and 2. Bundesliga [[Holstein Kiel]] on penalties in the second round. <ref>{{cite web |title=DFB-POKAL |url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2301983 |accessdate=3 November 2019}}</ref>, before losing 1\u20130 to [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=DFB-POKAL |url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2302011 |accessdate=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Relegation and Non-Qualification===\nIn 2003, a 15th-place finish in the Regionalliga Nord (III) saw the team relegated for the first time in over thirty years. Some dispute surrounds Verl having to play the last game of the season in Paderborn during torrential rain, while [[Hamburger SV II]] were able to claim unplayable conditions and played the next day, securing a victory against [[KFC Uerdingen]] to remain in the league.<ref>[http://www.fussballdaten.de/regionalliga/nord/2003/ Regionalliga Nord 2002/03, 34th gameday]</ref>\n\nSC Verl had to play the [[Oberliga (football)|Oberliga Westfalen]] (IV) for four years before winning the championship and advancing to Regionalliga again in 2007. One season later, the [[3. Liga]] was introduced between the [[2. Bundesliga]] and the Regionalliga, which in turn was split up from two into three divisions. SC Verl suffered through a poor 2007\u201308 campaign, finishing 18th and failing to qualify for the 3. Liga. They have remained in the fourth-tier Regionalliga since.\n\n===[[2009 European football betting scandal]]===\nTwo SC Verl games from the 2008\u201309 season&nbsp;\u2013 among over two hundred games by other clubs&nbsp;\u2013 were suspected of having been rigged by players, leading to significant attention by the press as, for several days, SC Verl was the only club actually named. The two players accused were summarily suspended, and their contracts were eventually terminated.<ref>[http://www.rootdirectory.de/scv/20091217.html Neumanns Platz im Verler Kader ist frei]{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} in: ''Neue Westf\u00e4lische'', 17 December 2009</ref><ref>[http://www.scv-fans.de/03c1989d290cc7b01.php SC Verl k\u00fcndigt Hagedorn'']{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} in: ''Westfalenblatt'', 24 February 2010</ref>\n\n===Amateur success===\nHaving played at least fourth tier level since 1970, with 17 consecutive seasons in the third tier, makes SC Verl one of the most consistent top teams of Germany's amateur football. One of the smallest cities to field a fourth-tier football team, and together with neighbouring club [[SC Wiedenbr\u00fcck 2000]] one of only two clubs in the [[Regionalliga West]] working under amateur conditions (both players and coaches have day-time jobs), the club is without any liabilities&nbsp;\u2013 a direct result of a continued policy of \"no credit financing\".\n\nSince 2008 the club has been a member of the Regionalliga West, achieving mid-table finishes each season.\n\n<timeline>\n\nImageSize = width:850 height:165\nPlotArea  = width:700 height:40 left:130 bottom:65\nAlignBars = justify\n\nPeriod     = from:1970 till:2018\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nScaleMajor = unit:year increment:4 start:1970\nScaleMinor = unit:year increment:1 start:1970\n\nColors =\n  id:gruen value:rgb(0.7,1,0.7)\n  id:blau  value:rgb(0.7,0.7,1)\n  id:rot   value:rgb(1,0.7,0.7)\n  id:blau  value:rgb(0.5,0.5,1)\n  id:gelb  value:rgb(1,1,0.7)\n  id:grau  value:gray(0.8)\n\nBarData =\n  bar:3rdtier text:\"3rd Tier\"\n  bar:4thtier text:\"4th Tier\"\n\nPlotData=\n  align:center textcolor:black fontsize:8 mark:(line,grau) width:20 shift:(1,-5)\n\n  bar:3rdtier color:gruen\n  from:1986 till:1987 text:9\n  from:1987 till:1988 text:13\n  from:1988 till:1989 text:7\n  from:1989 till:1990 text:6\n  from:1990 till:1991 text:1\n  from:1991 till:1992 text:3\n  from:1992 till:1993 text:2\n  from:1993 till:1994 text:5\n  from:1994 till:1995 text:2\n  from:1995 till:1996 text:10\n  from:1996 till:1997 text:7\n  from:1997 till:1998 text:10\n  from:1998 till:1999 text:10\n  from:1999 till:2000 text:9\n  from:2000 till:2001 text:6\n  from:2001 till:2002 text:11\n  from:2002 till:2003 text:15\n  from:2007 till:2008 text:18\n\n  bar:4thtier color:gelb\n  from:1970 till:1971 text:3\n  from:1971 till:1972 text:6\n  from:1972 till:1973 text:3\n  from:1973 till:1974 text:3\n  from:1974 till:1975 text:7\n  from:1975 till:1976 text:7\n  from:1976 till:1977 text:7\n  from:1977 till:1978 text:2\n  from:1978 till:1979 text:4\n  from:1979 till:1980 text:5\n  from:1980 till:1981 text:2\n  from:1981 till:1982 text:8\n  from:1982 till:1983 text:4\n  from:1983 till:1984 text:4\n  from:1984 till:1985 text:2\n  from:1985 till:1986 text:1\n  from:2003 till:2004 text:2\n  from:2004 till:2005 text:5\n  from:2005 till:2006 text:2\n  from:2006 til